args:
The prince and his friends storm the city square,
interrupting Tiana's execution. He pledges the
support of New Alberia to Aquaphos in exchange
for Tiana's continued livelihood. Thus do bonds
forged save the undersea kingdom from crisis.
I am victorious because I do not fight\nalone, but with the aid of my friends.
That is why you won't be entrusting your\npower only to me, Leviathan.
You'll be entrusting it to all of us.
You have shown me your potential.\nYou are indeed a ray of light to illuminate\nmy path out of this lonely abyss.
Here we forge our pact—one that crosses\nthe boundary 'tween land and sea!
And with this pactstone, the deed is done.
Our crisis ends at long last, and with it,\nLeviathan is free. What a relief.
I may never see the future I dreamed of,\nbut it does my heart good to know that the\nfuture of the abyssians is in safe hands.
I leave the rest to you, my friends.\nThank you.
What was all that? Where's Tiana off to?
And now, the treasonous priestess Tiana\nwill pay for her crimes with her life!
(I'd be lying if I said I wasn't afraid. But...)
Look, Tiana. It's normal to feel afraid\nwhen the stakes are so high.
But facing challenges head-on is precisely\nwhat helps us grow stronger.
(Decision-making used to paralyze me.\nI was powerless—devoid of agency. Now\nI'm strong enough to stand by my choices.)
(I have no regrets about meeting Alex\nand Mym.)
(The bonds I've forged are as currents,\nflowing out to the wide world beyond.\nThey are irreplaceable to me.)
Step forth, wayward priestess of the abyss!
I am the ruler of the kingdom of New\nAlberia, your neighbor on the surface.\nI am called {player_name}.
In the midst of your crisis with Leviathan,\nI earned his acknowledgment, and the two\nof us forged a pact.
What is the meaning of this?!
I know that your people are on the brink\nof ruin.
And so I offer to you a proposal!
Stay your hand in the execution of the\npriestess Tiana, and let her be free.
In exchange, I will offer my full support\nto this kingdom!
But those who reside above the waves\nabandoned us a thousand years ago.

There is no need for your ruin OR for
conflict. All you have to do is release
Tiana, and I promise we shall form an
equal-footed diplomatic alliance.
The people of the surface may well have\ntreated you with cruelty a millennium ago.
But times can change. We ourselves\ncan be the instruments of that change.\nWe must be!
You would truly aid us?\nYou do not desire conflict?
I...never thought I'd live to see the day.
I can scarcely believe my ears.
On that day, a ray of light shone down from the\nsurface into the ocean deep.
Tiana's execution was called off, and an agreement\nwas forged between Aquaphos and New Alberia.
In one stroke, the abyssians averted their\ndestruction and entered a harmonious new\nera with their allies above the water.
Mym, Alex, everyone...\nFrom the bottom of my heart, thank you!
I never would have dared hope that you\nwould come to my rescue.
Don't be absurd! I could never let the\nperson who saved our lives die without\nlifting a finger to help.
Hee hee. Well, if you're going to put it that\nway, now you're the ones who saved MY\nlife.
But are you sure you don't regret making\nan agreement of that scale just for me?

I find the whole thing quite fortuitous,
really. Not only have we discovered the
Kingdom of the Deep, but we've made
allies of them.

Your people have cultivated a great many
impressive technologies in order to live on
the seafloor. I suspect they will be of
considerable use to us as well.
Er... I think what Chelle is trying to say\nis ＂don't worry about it.＂
So be it. Still, I can't thank you enough,\n{player_name}.
Heeey, repairs to the Gran Fiore are all\ndone!
We're ready to set sail anytime!
A shame that you're leaving already.
Yes. But we'll be sending envoys in\nshort order.

And they're gonna be LOADED with food
and other stuff from the surface, so get
those taste buds primed for earthly
excellence, my undersea amigo!
Once reconstruction of Aquaphos is\nfinished, may I come to the surface\nto see you?
You fought for us abyssians, after all.
I'd like to return the favor. If there's\nany way I can make myself useful—
Oh, listen to yourself, would you?
We're FRIENDS now. You don't have to ask.\nYou can come anytime you want!
I'll be looking forward to our next\nencounter, Tiana.
Even if we're apart, our bonds remain.\nThey will endure, deep and vast as the sea.
Now that you mention it, it sounds a bit\nlike a bell ringing.
It's like the ocean itself is blessing us.
The peal of the bell rang on and on,\ncommemorating the birth of a new friendship.
